      "solution": "n = int(input())\nboard = []\n\n# Read in the board to the 2d list\nfor i in range(n):\n    board += [list(input())]\n\n# Run through each square of the board\nfor row in range(n):\n    for col in range(n):\n        # If it isnt a mine, we have to assign a number\n        if board[row][col] != '*':\n            total = 0\n            # Loop through surrounding squares, and if they are in the board and a mine, add\n            for r in range(row-1,row+2):\n                for c in range(col-1,col+2):\n                    if 0<=r<n and 0<=c<n and board[r][c]=='*' and (r!=row or c!=col):\n                        total+=1\n            # Store the total\n            board[row][col] = str(total)\n\n# Output the board with the mine counts inserted\nfor row in board:\n    print(''.join(row))",
